_Two_Alter", "agent_output": "```python\ndef is_Two_Alter(s: str) -> bool:\n    # If string length is less than 2, it cannot alternate between two characters\n    if len(s) < 2:\n        return False\n    \n    # Extract the two characters that should alternate\n    char1 = s[0]\n    char2 = None\n    \n    # Find the second character different from char1\n    for ch in s[1:]:\n        if ch != char1:\n            char2 = ch\n            break\n    \n    # If no second character found, string is made of only one character\n    if char2 is None:\n        return False\n    \n    # Check if string contains only these two characters\n    for ch in s:\n        if ch != char1 and ch != char2:\n            return False\n    \n    # Check if characters alternate properly\n    for i in range(len(s)):\n        if i % 2 == 0 and s[i] != char1:\n            return False\n        if i % 2 == 1 and s[i] != char2:\n            return False\n    \n    return True\n\n# Assertions to test the function\nassert is_Two_Alter(\"abab\") == True\nassert is_Two_Alter(\"aaaa\") == False\nassert is_Two_Alter(\"xyz\") == False\n```"}
